 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-DATALOG: Datalog evaluator termination and negation guards. CONTEXT: query/evaluator.rs (1,786 LOC) has two gaps: (1) No termination guard — fixpoint iteration on recursive rules over cyclic graphs produces unbounded tuples. OOM kill is the only termination mechanism. (2) No negation guard — if a query with negation-as-failure is submitted, behavior is undefined. 28 unwrap() calls on variable lookups from user-provided bindings can panic on malformed queries. RATIONALE: The evaluator is exposed to user input via 'braid query --datalog'. Unbounded recursion and panics on bad input are denial-of-service vectors. The negation gap is a correctness issue — wrong results are worse than errors. APPROACH: (1) Add max_tuples parameter to evaluate_with_frontier() with default 100_000. If the result set exceeds this limit during fixpoint iteration, return Err(QueryError::TupleLimitExceeded { limit, actual }). (2) Add query validation pass before evaluation: scan all clauses for negation (not yet parsed, but guard against future additions). If negated clauses detected, return Err(QueryError::NegationNotSupported). (3) Replace 28 unwrap() calls in evaluator.rs with .ok_or(QueryError::UnboundVariable { name })? — proper error propagation. (4) Add test: recursive transitive closure query on 3-node cycle with max_tuples=100 — verify TupleLimitExceeded error. (5) Add test: query with unbound variable — verify UnboundVariable error (not panic). ACCEPTANCE: (A) TupleLimitExceeded error returned for runaway queries. (B) Existing non-recursive queries unaffected (limits never hit). (C) No unwrap() calls remain in evaluate_with_frontier(). (D) Malformed query produces error, not panic. (E) All existing query tests pass. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/query/evaluator.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-QUERY-001 (fixpoint convergence), INV-QUERY-008 (FFI boundary purity)."
